HEADWORD: Brie cheese
<hw>Brie" cheese`</hw> <pr>(br⟦emac⟧" ch⟦emac⟧z`)</pr>. <def>A kind of
soft French cream cheese; -- so called from the district in France where
it is made; it is milder than Camembert; -- called also <altname>fromage
de Brie</altname>, <altname>Brie</altname> and <altname>brie</altname>
(uncapitalized).</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source> + <source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Brief</ent>⟦br⟧
